🧿 Looking for Summer break activities Georgia? Then watch this reel to witness the best aquarium in North America! 

Things to note:
1. Book your dolphin presentation and sea lion presentation in advance.
2. Plan on spening atleast 3-4 hours there.
3. They do have live dolphin, sea lion, penguin encounters where you can touch the animals as well. Make sure to book it 2-3 weeks in advance.
4. The fish tunnel was our most favourite.
5. Make loads of memories :)

Book your experience through @fever_us today!

🧿 Looking for fun summer break activities. Then swipe right to see more!  Tell me which activity you would like to do first! 

1️⃣ Fly Heli Atlanta - They provide helicopter rides over Atlanta with stunning views of the down town. Excellent for a bday gift, Anniversary gift.
2️⃣ Sling Shot Rental - Super thrilling experience where you can rent a slingshot and drive around the city with your favourite music and loved one.
3️⃣ Mary Alice Park - Perfect for a picnic by the lake. Kayaking, Grilling & totally fun vibes.
4️⃣ Vickery Creek waterfall - Go for a hike, enjoy the stunning views of the waterfall or simply enjoy the sounds of the lake! One of a perfect mix of relaxation and stunning views.
5️⃣ Warbington Farms - Our personal favourite. Be it strawberry picking or simply fun park! Perfect place for all age groups.
6️⃣ Museum of Illusions - One of the most unique places I have ever visited! Super fun and mysterious.
